parts.text:
**Asian**

* **Soups:**
    * Pho (Vietnamese beef noodle soup)
    * Tom Yum (Thai spicy and sour soup)
    * Miso (Japanese soybean paste soup)
    * Samgyeopsal (Korean pork belly soup)
    * Laksa (Singaporean spicy coconut milk noodle soup)
* **Stews:**
    * Beef Rendang (Indonesian spicy beef stew)
    * Massaman Curry (Thai peanut-based chicken stew)
    * Oyakodon (Japanese chicken and egg rice bowl)
    * Bulgogi (Korean grilled marinated beef strips)
* **Hot Drinks:**
    * Matcha (Japanese green tea)
    * Dalgona Coffee (Korean whipped iced coffee)
    * Yuzu Tea (Japanese citrus fruit tea)
    * Sakura Tea (Japanese cherry blossom tea)

**Mediterranean**

* **Soups:**
    * Gazpacho (Spanish cold tomato soup)
    * Minestrone (Italian vegetable soup)
    * Avgolemono (Greek lemon-egg soup)
    * Harira (Moroccan tomato and lentil soup)
    * Bouillabaisse (French fish stew)
* **Stews:**
    * Tagine (North African meat and vegetable stew)
    * Paella (Spanish saffron rice dish)
    * Moussaka (Greek eggplant and mince casserole)
    * Cassoulet (French bean and meat stew)
* **Hot Drinks:**
    * Turkish Coffee
    * Greek Coffee
    * Arabic Coffee
    * Salep (Turkish flour-based beverage)
    * RakÄ± (Turkish anise-flavored liqueur)
